A data analysis and visualization project tracking COVID-19 cases, recoveries, and deaths globally using publicly available datasets.

Project Objectives

- Collect and clean up-to-date COVID-19 data from trusted sources  
- Analyze trends in cases, recoveries, and fatalities by country and region  
- Visualize data to better understand the pandemicâ€™s progression worldwide  
- Provide insights for policymakers and the general public

Tools and Libraries Used

- Python 3.x  
- Pandas (data processing)  
- Matplotlib & Seaborn (visualizations)  
- Jupyter Notebook (interactive development)  
- Requests / API clients (data fetching)  
- Git & GitHub (version control and collaboration)

Insights and Reflections
- The project highlights how different countries experienced varied outbreak timelines and recovery rates.  
- Visualizations revealed waves of infections corresponding to new variants and policy changes.  
- Real-time tracking tools like this are vital for timely public health decisions.  
- Challenges included inconsistent data reporting and the need for frequent updates.  
- Future improvements could integrate vaccination data and mobility trends for richer analysis.
